cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NA, cs.IT

This paper deals with data in the form of symmetric positive definite (SPD) matrices, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses dictionary learning and sparse coding, which are techniques used in machine learning and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also formulates a novel Riemannian optimization objective, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper presents a computationally simple algorithm, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
